{
  "texts": [
    "The simplicity of explicit probability ensures that it can be applied in any advanced prompt engineering techniques such as Chain-of-Thought (CoT) 22, retrieval augmented generation (RAG) 23, 24, self consistency 25, and LLM agents 26, 27.",
    "However, given the challenges LLMs face with numerical reasoning 28, 29, the reliability of text-generated explicit probability values may be questionable and has not yet been thoroughly examined.",
    "On the other hand, several works have delved into the LLM-based methods of probability prediction 21, 30, which we define as \"implicit probability\".",
    "For example, for the question \"Given the following lab reports: [lab report text].",
    "Does the patient have COVID?"
  ]
}